sample.title: Meta moves to distance Manus from China links following acquisition
sample.description: CNBC’s MacKenzie Sigalos reports on Meta’s plan to reposition Manus — a startup founded in China and now based in Singapore — as it tries to build a clearer AI revenue story beyond ads while limiting geopolitical and regulatory blowback from the company’s origins and early backers.

sample.title: Meta buys Manus to scale AI agents across its platform
sample.description: CNBC’s MacKenzie Sigalos reports on Meta’s push to show an AI payoff beyond ad targeting, as it adds a fast-growing subscription agents business and faces rising scrutiny over its spending.

sample.title: Meta adds $18 billion in value on report of $2 billion Manus acquisition
sample.description: CNBC's MacKenzie Sigalos joins 'Halftime Report' to discuss why investors are cheering the purchase of a China-founded, Singapore-based AI agents company — and how it strengthens Meta’s business tools as questions mount about ROI.
